 	// We can only support async resets here. A lot of the stuff in init must happen on the EmuThread,
 	// and we are not on it here.
 	System_PostUIMessage(UIMessage::REQUEST_GAME_RESET);
 
+	// emucap: in headless the reset runs on the emu-thread run loop (there is no UI message pump).
+	// Block until that reboot actually completes so the client's ack means "rebooted", not merely
+	// "reset queued" — otherwise game.reset would look successful while nothing happened. The reboot's
+	// PSP_Shutdown takes the WS lifecycle lock (its STOPPING notification), which the dispatch is
+	// holding for us right now, so we drop it for the wait and reacquire before returning (else the
+	// blocked handler would deadlock the reboot). No-op in GUI builds — the mode is never enabled and
+	// the UI pump handles the reset itself.
+	if (Core_HeadlessResetMode()) {
